ZH: 请你去沏一壶茶。
EN: Please go make a pot of tea.

ZH: 我想沏一杯咖啡。
EN: I want to brew a cup of coffee.

ZH: 他正在沏绿茶。
EN: He is brewing green tea.

ZH: 她喜欢每天早上沏咖啡。
EN: She likes to brew coffee every morning.

ZH: 你可以沏红茶吗？
EN: Can you brew black tea?

ZH: 这种茶需要沏五分钟。
EN: This tea needs to brew for five minutes.

ZH: 我会用手沏茶。
EN: I will brew tea using my hands.

ZH: 她常常沏一壶花草茶。
EN: She often brews a pot of herbal tea.

ZH: 他心情不好，需要沏杯红茶。
EN: He is in a bad mood and needs to brew a cup of black tea.

ZH: 我用温水沏绿茶。
EN: I brew green tea with warm water.

ZH: 在中国，泡茶叫沏茶。
EN: In China, making tea is called "brewing tea".

ZH: 我可以来沏个咖啡吗？
EN: Can I come to make a coffee?

ZH: 我会用矿泉水来沏茶。
EN: I will use mineral water to brew tea.

ZH: 你可以教我如何正确沏茶吗？
EN: Can you teach me how to properly brew tea?

ZH: 他喜欢在早晨沏一壶热茶。
EN: He likes to brew a pot of hot tea in the morning.

ZH: 您想要一杯刚沏好的咖啡吗？
EN: Would you like a freshly brewed coffee?

ZH: 我每天早上都会沏一壶茶。
EN: I brew a pot of tea every morning.

ZH: 你会用热水来沏茶吗？
EN: Will you use hot water to brew tea?

ZH: 我用三分钟来沏一壶茶。
EN: I use three minutes to brew a pot of tea.

ZH: 他很会沏茶，每次都很好喝。
EN: He is very good at brewing tea, it tastes good every time.
